sprint: S06
track: B
task: B1
title: "fix(navigation): eliminate circular redirect loop on parts-diagrams desktop"
repos: [crop-front]
priority: high
refs:
  - meetup-02-06-26 ("click open parts diagram right there... it'll go back here again")
  - meetup-02-06-26 ("there's a lot of just going back to some of these menus")
requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND]

impact: |
  John demonstrated a case where clicking "Open parts diagram" from the assembly list
  sent the user back to the same menu they came from. This circular path is the #1
  navigation pain point: users with a known model can't reach their diagram in a
  straight line. Fixing it is a prerequisite for the V2 "easily usable" bar.

description: |
  Root-cause investigation required before coding. Trace the circular path:

  1. Start at /parts-diagrams (NH root) or /parts-diagrams/ferris.
  2. Select a model → /parts-diagrams/ferris/{modelCode}.
  3. Click an assembly → /parts-diagrams/ferris/assemblies/{assemblyCode}.
  4. From the assembly page, find any "back" / "open diagram" / "breadcrumb" link
     that routes back to step 2 or step 1 instead of going to the assembly viewer.

  Likely suspects:
  - `assembly-nav.tsx`: the back-navigation component on the assembly page.
  - `BrandBreadcrumb` in brand-assembly-view: does the breadcrumb href resolve
    correctly for non-NH brands?
  - `resolve-assembly-nav.ts`: derives the back-link from assembly context; if the
    brandCode is missing or wrong for non-NH brands the resolved href may be stale.
  - `ConditionalSchematicBanner` on brand pages: the CTA may route back to the
    diagrams root instead of the brand-specific diagrams page.

  Fix: ensure every "back" / "breadcrumb" link on the assembly page routes
  forward-only (brand landing → model list → assembly → schematic). Never loop.

scope:
  in:
    - Identify and fix the circular link(s) in the assembly viewer nav path
    - Verify breadcrumb depth at each step: landing → type → model → assembly ≤ 4 crumbs
    - Fix for both NH and non-NH brands (the non-NH path is more likely broken)
    - Unit test: `resolve-assembly-nav.ts` — for a non-NH brand assembly, resolves
      to /parts-diagrams/{brand}/{modelCode}, not /parts-diagrams root
  out:
    - Redesigning the breadcrumb component (layout/visual changes)
    - Changing the URL structure

invariants:
  - No page-level permanentRedirect() — edge-level only (see proxy.ts contract in CLAUDE.md)
  - Breadcrumb hrefs must be built with URL helpers, never inline template literals

acceptance:
  - From /parts-diagrams/ferris/assemblies/{assemblyCode}: clicking breadcrumb
    "Ferris" goes to /parts-diagrams/ferris, not /parts-diagrams
  - From /parts-diagrams/ferris/{modelCode}: no link routes back to the same page
  - Smoke test: navigate brand landing → type group → model → assembly → schematic
    with no circular step at any level (desktop Chrome, mobile Safari)

dep: A3 (smoke run reveals which brand triggers the loop)
output: features/assemblies/resolve-assembly-nav.ts fix + unit test update
